<!-- ============================================================ 02 EXECUTIVE SUMMARY ============================================================ -->
<section class="section" id="s02">
  <div class="sec-hdr">
    <div class="sec-num">Section 02</div>
    <div class="sec-title">Executive Summary</div>
    <div class="sec-sub">Complete standalone investment case — fund overview, structure, collateral, pipeline, returns, fees, and principal alignment</div>
    <div class="gold-rule"></div>
  </div>

  <div class="cio-letter">
    <div style="font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:9px;letter-spacing:.2em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--gold-dim);margin-bottom:26px;">Letter from the CIO — To Institutional Investors Evaluating Draft Horse Capital Partners</div>
    <p class="cio-para">I will be direct about what this fund is, what it is not, and why I structured it the way I did. Draft Horse Capital Partners is a single-mandate secured private credit vehicle. It is not diversified across multiple borrowers or strategies. It does not deploy into an origination pipeline we are building after close. It is one credit facility — $100 million — extended to a single institutional PE sponsor against a five-layer collateral package I designed specifically to minimize recovery exposure if that borrower cannot or will not perform. I describe it this way at the outset because institutional allocators reviewing this document deserve precision, not a narrative that defers concentration risk to footnote disclosures.</p>
    <p class="cio-para">The concentration is a deliberate underwriting decision, not a structural limitation. I know this borrower. I have evaluated their operations, their assets, and their incentives directly. I negotiated the lending terms, the covenant package, and the collateral architecture personally. I have equity exposure on both sides of this transaction — in the credit facility structure and in the aviation assets that serve as hard collateral. My capital is deployed alongside investor capital in the same position. I do not manage this fund from a distance, and I am not compensated by fees on committed capital regardless of performance. My economic interest derives entirely from the spread between what the PE sponsor pays the Fund and what the Fund pays investors. That structure means my incentive is to maximize deployment, maintain covenant compliance, and generate more spread — not to collect a management fee on idle capital.</p>
    <p class="cio-para">The five-layer collateral architecture — operating cash flows, physical real estate and inventory, 100% portfolio company equity, Gulfstream G550 aviation assets under UCC-1 and FAA Registry perfected first lien, and a PE sponsor guaranty from an entity with equity exposure on both sides — was constructed to ensure that each layer is independently enforceable, independently recoverable, and structurally uncorrelated to the other layers in the ways that matter most in a stress scenario. In a default event, the Fund does not need all five layers to hold. It needs one. The recovery analysis under any stress case I have modeled is materially superior to single-collateral private credit structures, which remain the market standard at this scale.</p>
    <p class="cio-para">The 17% target yield at the top commitment tier is the product of the structure, not a backward calculation from what sounds attractive to investors. The borrower is willing to pay a premium rate for a direct, relationship-sourced, collateral-backed facility that provides operational certainty without bank intermediary fees or restrictive bank covenants. Investors receive a fixed portion of that spread. The Fund retains the balance. No management fee is charged. No carried interest is taken. I present Draft Horse to qualified institutional allocators as a documented, collateral-secured credit opportunity with a known borrower, a fully structured facility, and a quantifiable five-layer recovery framework. I am prepared to support every element of this presentation with documentation under appropriate confidentiality protocols.</p>
    <div class="cio-sig"><div class="cio-name">Caleb Caraway</div><div class="cio-title">CIO — Dark Horse Wealth Management &nbsp;|&nbsp; Managing Partner — Draft Horse Capital Partners LLC</div></div>
  </div>

  <div class="stat-grid">
    <div class="stat-box"><div class="stat-val">9–17%</div><div class="stat-lbl">Target Yield (Tiered, Fixed)</div></div>
    <div class="stat-box"><div class="stat-val">$100M</div><div class="stat-lbl">Active Pipeline — Identified</div></div>
    <div class="stat-box"><div class="stat-val">5</div><div class="stat-lbl">Independent Collateral Layers</div></div>
    <div class="stat-box"><div class="stat-val">Zero</div><div class="stat-lbl">Management Fees / Carry</div></div>
    <div class="stat-box"><div class="stat-val">Qtrly</div><div class="stat-lbl">Distribution Frequency</div></div>
    <div class="stat-box"><div class="stat-val">36 Mo</div><div class="stat-lbl">Term · 100% Principal Return</div></div>
  </div>

  <div class="content">
    <div class="card card-gold">
      <h3>Fund Description</h3>
      <p>Draft Horse Capital Partners LLC is a Texas-domiciled, Reg D 506(c) private credit fund providing a single $100 million structured senior secured credit facility to one institutional PE sponsor. The Fund is secured by five independently enforceable collateral layers under perfected UCC-1 financing statements and FAA Civil Aviation Registry notations. The Fund distributes fixed tiered yields of 9%–17% per annum to investors quarterly, returns 100% of principal at 36-month maturity, and charges zero management fees and zero carried interest. The borrower is identified, the facility is structured, and deployment begins on first close.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="two-col">
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Investment Highlights</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Fixed tiered yield:</strong> 9%–17% p.a., quarterly distributions — rate locked at subscription tier for full 36-month term</li>
          <li><strong>Five-layer collateral:</strong> Operating cash flows → real estate/inventory → 100% equity pledge → G550 aviation fleet → PE sponsor guaranty. Each layer independently enforceable.</li>
          <li><strong>Zero fee structure:</strong> No management fee, no carried interest, no waterfall. GP earns through spread above investor yield only.</li>
          <li><strong>Day-one deployment:</strong> No ramp period — $100M facility ready to draw on fund close. First distribution accrues from first day capital is accepted.</li>
          <li><strong>Hard asset aviation collateral:</strong> Gulfstream G550s independently appraised at $30–45M each, under dual UCC-1 and FAA Registry first lien — globally marketable.</li>
          <li><strong>Institutional infrastructure:</strong> NAV Fund Services (admin), Spicer Jeffries LLP (audit/tax), Axos Bank (banking), SCALE LLP (securities counsel).</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Key Terms Summary</h3>
        <ul class="lv-list">
          <li><span class="lv-lbl">Minimum Subscription</span><span class="lv-val td-gold">$200,000</span></li>
